Description: An encampment outside Alexandria, plate 4 of four plates; view with three cannons along the wall in the foreground, soldiers standing beside the cannons, a hill on the centre horizon, city on the right in the bay. 1804 Aquatint and etching, printed in dark brown ink
Producer name: Print made by: Frederick Christian Lewis (aquatint)
Associated events: Associated Event: Battle of the Nile August 1-2 1798
